track_notes:
This is the TrackBack info as recorded off my GPS.

The initial part of the route follows a faint path picking up the old road around NG996025 which quickly disappears into the raised Loch Quoich (Note: if the Loch is low it maybe possible to utilise the old road from the existing road to this point). You are now onto a rough path to around NG964010 where you again pick up a road which takes you around to the dam. From there stike out and ascend the Ben as shown.

Its a long hard route so be prepared for a long day.

Take care and enjoy yourself.

73

Jack(;>J
